quest.name: Shadowed Pasts Once More
journal: The Radiant scout is keeping a close eye on the sullen-eyed voidsent.

You are conversing with the sullen-eyed voidsent at the Hall of the Radiant Host when the being suddenly senses the rest of itself in the city. As before, there are four of them all told, and as before, you are tasked with tracking them down and sending them back to rejoin themselves.

You have located all four remaining wayward hecteyes, from whom you learn about the pasts of two mighty voidsent─none other than your erstwhile foes, the archfiends Cagnazzo and Rubicante. With your task thus accomplished, you make your way back to the Hall of the Radiant Host.

Having been reunited with all of its selves, the sullen-eyed voidsent is finally whole again. And thanks to its ability to see its kind from a great distance, it seems likely to find employment with the Radiant Host, thus allowing it to fulfill its dream of abiding in the Source. Voidsent were once people in the past, and they may yet have a future. As the creature sets a hopeful gaze upon the road ahead, you cannot help but wonder what lies in store for it.

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: Ah, if it isn't MistressMaster Forename. Since last we spoke, I have continued keeping an eye on the voidsent.

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: While the creatures have given me no reason to believe that they pose a danger, the rest of them remain at large.

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: My fellows and I have yet to come by any eyewitness information, but their forms being what they are, they cannot have gotten far. Of course, it would make our search easier if they were likewise drawn to Radz-at-Han...

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: My other selves have been telling me about their adventures. Truly, your world is a fascinating place!

dialogue.name: Q1
dialogue.text: What will you say?

dialogue.name: A1
dialogue.text: There's nothing like exploring a new city.

dialogue.name: A1
dialogue.text: Your world is fascinating too.

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: You've seen a lot of this world, have you not? I wish to do the same, and travel to all sorts of places!

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: Once I've found the rest of me, that is... It would be unthinkable to leave even a sliver of myself out of the experience.

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: So you've enjoyed hearing my tales? I would be glad to share more with you.

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: Once I've found the rest of me, that is... The others have more knowledge of mighty voidsent, you see.

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: Hm? This sensation... Could it be...?

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: Yes, I feel them! The rest of myself! They're very close now!

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: There's four of them, and unless I'm mistaken, they're somewhere in the city. Please find them for me, that I might be whole again!

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: As before, by way of payment, they will tell you about powerful voidsent and their pasts.

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: Now, the nearest appears to be this way. Perhaps that's a good place to start.

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: The rest of its fellows have appeared in the city? Then you had best track them down!

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: Judging by the direction, I expect the nearest one is in Dharma. I leave the creatures in your capable hands!

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: Worry not, I will see to it that these ones do not wander off. Best of luck finding their fellows!

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: The others will have seen some sights of their own. How I look forward to hearing their tales!

dialogue.name: SYSTEM
dialogue.text: You have found the last of the voidsent. Time to head back to the Hall of the Radiant Host.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: You've been looking for me, you say? Sorry for the trouble. I found a place with beautiful water and thought I'd have a rollick, but ended up being washed away...

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: I tried to get back upstream, swimming against the flow, and had managed to come this far when you appeared.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: After all that effort, I'd like nothing more than to reunite with my other selves. But if you've been promised a tale, then you shall have one!

dialogue.name: FISHERA04661
dialogue.text: <sigh> Nothing but small fry...

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: See that mortal there? He fished me up, but promptly released me while calling me a “hideous slug.” I don't know what that was about, but it worked out well enough.

dialogue.name: FISHERA04661
dialogue.text: Oh, to be out in the open sea and catch something big...

dialogue.name: FISHERA04661
dialogue.text: But until I can afford a halfway decent rod, I'll just have to put up with this tired old fishing hole... <sigh>

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: I know the feeling well. The desire to chase after big fish. I used to be a fisherman too, you see. Together with my brother.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: But the Contramemoria wreaked havoc on the ocean's aether, and nary any fish remained to be caught. Each morning we would wake up not knowing whether we'd have food to fill our bellies.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)On a day like so many before, we were waiting in vain for a bite. My brother's face was fixed in a grimace, and I assumed he was cursing the war in his mind. But it turned out he was thinking about something else altogether. And when he finally spoke, the frustration was plain in his voice.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)“Even if there were fish to catch, is this how I'm going to live out my days? Sitting endlessly with a pole in hand? It's like dying a slow death, and I can't take it anymore.”

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)More so than our privation, it was the mundane, unchanging nature of our lives that bothered him.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)In the next instant he blurted out, “That's it─if there's a war, I'm going to fight too! That way I won't be bored, at least!”

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)And just like that, he threw aside his rod and set off. Right into the thick of the conflict...

dialogue.name: MEMORIAMASTERA04661
dialogue.text: D-Damn it!

dialogue.name: MEMORIAMASTERB04661
dialogue.text: It's over!

dialogue.name: MEMORIAMASTERB04661
dialogue.text: Ungh... Wh-Who the hells are you!?

dialogue.name: MEMORIAMASTERA04661
dialogue.text: Whoever you are, I'm in your debt. Having exhausted my powers, I was all but defeated, but now none remain to oppose me here.

dialogue.name: MEMORIAMASTERA04661
dialogue.text: Perhaps you would consider serving me? You would be well rewarded, of course. I could grant you riches, castles...

dialogue.name: MEMORIAMASTERA04661
dialogue.text: Wh-What's the meaning of this!? Weren't you a friend!?

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: Friend? I'm just after some excitement. So come on, give it to me!

dialogue.name: FISHERB04661
dialogue.text: There you are, thank heavens! What were you thinking, taking on memoriates with your bare fists? However strong you may be, you're lucky to be alive!

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: Alive...

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: Yes, I've never felt so...alive!

dialogue.name: FISHERB04661
dialogue.text: Wh-Where are you going?

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: No more chasing small fry for me. From now on, I'm going to live for the thrill of battle.

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: I'll seek out those stronger than me, and I'll give 'em all a taste of my fist!

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)“Never have I felt so alive as I did, risking life and limb,” he said as he strode away, never to return.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)Some time afterwards, a rumor reached me of a fearsome warrior. The man would arrive unannounced on a battlefield, trounce anyone and everyone indiscriminately, before disappearing again.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)Cagnazzo, he was called, and cursed for a feral dog. That was enough for me to know that my brother still lived.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: It was only when I became a voidsent that I came to understand my brother. To understand the emptiness he felt in his mundane life.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: It inspired me to want to break free from my own unchanging existence, and instilled in me a longing for this world.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: And for all his quirks, he was a good and kind brother, always looking out for me and helping me with my fishing.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Like everyone, he must have turned into a voidsent. If he had the chance to come here, I believe he would've found a purpose in life. A proper one.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Hehe, thanks to you, I could relive those old memories. And with that, I had best go and join my other selves. Be seeing you!

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Hm? What business does a mortal have with me?

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: So the rest of me are safe!? Thank goodness... It was worth risking myself to let the others escape.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: No sooner had we arrived in this world than we were attacked by fearsome creatures of stone. I drew their attention, and after scrambling hither and yon, managed to get myself to safety.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: But to so jealously guard treasure, you mortals must truly be fond of it. Lo─there's another place for storing it right there.

dialogue.name: SHIRAZADE
dialogue.text: They say it's mountain after mountain of treasure in there. We just need to find the coffers that act as portals.

dialogue.name: ADVENTURERA04661
dialogue.text: And then survive the guardians and deadly fiends... I don't like our chances with just the three of us.

dialogue.name: ADVENTURERB04661
dialogue.text: Less of us means a bigger share for each!

dialogue.name: SHIRAZADE
dialogue.text: Exactly. Besides, what's an adventure without a little danger?

dialogue.name: ADVENTURERA04661
dialogue.text: Hmmm... I'm really not sure about this...

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: To willingly throw oneself into danger... It's truly a strange mortal quirk. Unlike your kind, we voidsent are quite risk averse. For instance, we wouldn't think to challenge a stronger being.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Except for him, perhaps. An odd fellow who loved fighting for its own sake...

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: His name was Cagnazzo, and there was nothing he feared in his domain.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Employing deception, he trapped his foes and drowned them in a bottomless mire. It mattered not how strong they were. All fell before him.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Yet despite his victories, he never felt truly satisfied. And through a chance meeting, he would learn the reason why.

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: That you should repel my attack... You're tougher than I expected!

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)To whom do I speak?

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: I am Cagnazzo! And I'll bet you're the one they say is seeking out the strong. Well, if it's battle you want, then you need look no further!

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)Lest you misunderstand, I do not desire fruitless battle. On the contrary, 'twould seem that it is you who seek out the strong. Why?

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: When you're hungry, you devour. It doesn't matter who. Your luck ran out when you strolled into my domain!

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)None would so risk themselves simply because of an empty stomach. Nay, my friend. The source of your hunger lies elsewhere.

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: Wh-What is this aether, so pure and sublime!? There's so much of it I'm ripe to burst! And yet...

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: I still don't feel satisfied...

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)Do you see? 'Tis not for aether that you thirst, but battle.

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)You'll not quench this thirst with stagnant swamp water. Nay, naught save that of a raging torrent will sate you!

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: What do you mean?

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)There is no joy to be had in ensnaring your quarry. For victory to have savor, you must place yourself in the midst of danger.

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)If you join me, I shall see to it you never want for dread foes to grant you satisfaction. What say you?

dialogue.name: WATERMONOLITH
dialogue.text: Heh, why do I feel as though I've remembered something important? Whoever you are, I would know more.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: And thus did he find a place to belong─upon the fine line that divides the devourer and the devoured.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: If he could do battle with just one worthy foe, he told himself, he could go to his rest forever satisfied.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: From that day forth, Cagnazzo tirelessly sought out those who might be able to best him. Each time hoping for bliss, but knowing that, like as not, disappointment ultimately awaited.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: A yearning so strong, nothing else matters... Do you have such a thing driving you too, mortal?

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Looking back, it was extremely reckless of me to come to this world. But it has been worth every bit of danger and more.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Ahhh, I can't wait to share my experiences with myself! I'll be on my way now─thanks for coming to find me!

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: The rest of me are here too? What a relief! I was taking in the sights in a village nearby when I realized I had become separated...

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: I'm glad I decided to follow the clamor and head to this city. There are so many mortals here, so many beautiful buildings!

dialogue.name: BOY04661
dialogue.text: Father, what is this building?

dialogue.name: DAD04661
dialogue.text: This, my boy, is the resting place of the great Alzadaal.

dialogue.name: DAD04661
dialogue.text: Centuries ago, he journeyed here from the mainland, and helped to end the war between the Matanga tribes─an act which laid the foundation for the nation of Radz-at-Han.

dialogue.name: BOY04661
dialogue.text: So it's thanks to him that we all get along!

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Ah, a tomb. A place for mortals to remember their dead. It calls to mind people from my own past...

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: My mother, who died in the Contramemoria. And the ones who laid her to rest...

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)Long, long ago, there lived two powerful mages.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)It was said that none could match their might, yet they nevertheless continued to hone their skills at their training ground, atop a peak called Mount Ordeals.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)One day, fell fiends began attacking villages unprovoked. Upon hearing the grim tidings, the mages came to a resolution.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)“Through years of training, we have mastered our flames. 'Tis time for us to employ them for the salvation of the world.”

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)So it was that the pair descended the mountain, and set about vanquishing the fiends.

dialogue.name: FIREMONOLITH
dialogue.text: Just that one left!

dialogue.name: MAGE04661
dialogue.text: Leave it to me!

dialogue.name: GIRL04661
dialogue.text: (-Frightened Girl-)No! Don't!

dialogue.name: GIRL04661
dialogue.text: Please don't hurt her! Don't hurt my mother!

dialogue.name: MAGE04661
dialogue.text: Y-Your mother?

dialogue.name: MAGE04661
dialogue.text: Arrrgh!

dialogue.name: GIRL04661
dialogue.text: Please save her! I beg you!

dialogue.name: FIREMONOLITH
dialogue.text: Grrr... What do I do!?

dialogue.name: FIREMONOLITH
dialogue.text: It seems I have no choice...

dialogue.name: GIRL04661
dialogue.text: What? She's...she's turned into a crystal!

dialogue.name: FIREMONOLITH
dialogue.text: I said that I would save the world...but I couldn't save even a single life!

dialogue.name: FIREMONOLITH
dialogue.text: My flames were meant to be like the sun... They were meant to protect─to keep warm and light the way... And yet...and yet─!

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)In his great fury at his failings, the mage's face turned red as a ruby. Thus did the girl choose to call him Rubicante.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)The mage returned to his mountain, where he buried his comrade. Upon the gravestone he etched words of admonishment, and continued his training alone.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)One day, when visiting his comrade's grave, he found that a familiar crystal had been left there.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)Its presence lifted a great weight off his chest. Without words, it told him that that girl was grateful for what he did.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: (-Wayward Hecteye-)That day, he regained something he had lost. And descending the mountain once more, he embarked upon a journey, determined to use his powers for good.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: As sad as it is to lose a precious life, it's sadder still, I think, to lose one's purpose.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Mount Ordeals has been swallowed up by Darkness, and his comrade's grave with it. But wherever Rubicante may be, I like to believe that the little girl still remains in his heart...

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Well, it's past time I rejoined the others. It was nice talking to you, mortal!

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: ...What? I'm calling me, you say? I can appreciate my separation anxiety, but I answer to no one─not even myself.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: I am my own master. I do what I like, when I like. I will rejoin the others at my own leisurely pace.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Mortals, on the other hand, always seem to be busy at work. Short as your lives are, one would think you'd spend more time on leisure. You're truly strange creatures.

dialogue.name: ALCHEMIST04661
dialogue.text: Still burning strong, just like the start of the experiment...

dialogue.name: ALCHEMIST04661
dialogue.text: Ugh, by the Sisters, but tending the flame is mind-numbing work. Someone has to do it, I suppose, but I just wish it wasn't me...

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Tending the flame... That reminds me of a voidsent I once knew.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: He watched over a beacon fire, seeing to it that it remained ever lit. Unlike that mortal, however, he did it of his own volition.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Such an act served no practical purpose in our world─even if night and day existed, we voidsent don't rely upon light. Yet he persisted.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Though perplexed by his curious ritual, I somehow found myself helping him with it...

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Rubicante was his name, and he went about his task dutifully.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Others mocked him for his meaningless act.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: But it must have held some manner of meaning to him. And so, when I chanced to find the beacon guttered out, I made certain to let him know.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: For time out of mind this routine continued uninterrupted. Until that fateful day...

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)I see flames dancing in the distance; who should I find tending it but a mage of considerable might. With such power, surely you can do more than keep a beacon lit?

dialogue.name: FIREMONOLITH
dialogue.text: My flames serve not to smite others nor to sate my hunger.

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)Then what purpose do they serve?

dialogue.name: FIREMONOLITH
dialogue.text: I cannot say for certain...but to simply behold this flame somehow sets my heart at ease.

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)I see... 'Twould seem you lack the power to comprehend the feelings engraved upon your soul.

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)But such a lack is readily rectified.

dialogue.name: FIREMONOLITH
dialogue.text: This warmth, invigorating and comforting... Where have I felt it before?

dialogue.name: FIREMONOLITH
dialogue.text: Of course─the sun! That which once shone its light upon creation!

dialogue.name: FIREMONOLITH
dialogue.text: Though it would set, never did it fail to rise again. And like the sun, my flames must never die!

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)So that is the way of it. Through your flames, you sought to recreate the sun's journey. To recreate the world as it was before.

dialogue.name: FIREMONOLITH
dialogue.text: Who are you, who could unearth memories buried in the deepest recesses of my heart?

dialogue.name: BLACKKNIGHT
dialogue.text: (-Knight in Black-)It matters not who I am, but what I seek to do. Join me, and together we shall banish the Darkness and see that the sun rises again.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: According to the mysterious knight, the price to save the world was dear: the inhabitants of the neighboring reality must be sacrificed. To which Rubicante replied...

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: “I have sworn to use my power to save the world. If innocent souls must be consumed by my flames, then I shall bear responsibility for the sin.”

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: Thus did he choose his path─of his own volition. And his spirit lives on in me, as an undying flame.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: A world engulfed in Darkness had become the norm for me. But since coming here and basking in the sun, I've been reminded of all that we had lost.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: I understand Rubicante better now. Understand why he was willing to sacrifice all to restore the world to the way it was. To him, it was worth the price.

dialogue.name: VOIDSENT04660
dialogue.text: ...Well, I must say, it felt great to take a squirm down memory lane. With that, I shall now rejoin the others─of my own volition, of course!

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: One, two, three... Um, is this all of them, then?

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: You did it! You found all of me!

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: I trust I upheld my part of the bargain, and told you about more mighty voidsent?

dialogue.name: Q2
dialogue.text: What will you say?

dialogue.name: A2
dialogue.text: I learned about the pasts of Cagnazzo and Rubicante.

dialogue.name: A2
dialogue.text: Those voidsent fought fiercely, but they'll fight no more.

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: So you had already crossed paths with them... Though the tales may not help you in the battles ahead, I daresay they gave you something to think upon.

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: As mortals, then voidsent, then archfiends, these troubled souls fought with all their being. And now their fight is over...

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: Well, I myself have only heard the tales from the others. If I'm to make their feelings my own, I need to become whole again. Which I can now do, thanks to you.

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: So all of them are accounted for? Then by all means, let's have them return to the way they were.

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: Without further ado, then! To me, my selves!

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: At last, we're whole again! There's nothing we need fear!

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: And that which each of us experienced since coming here... It's as if I had experienced it all for myself!

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: I say it again, but this world is truly a fascinating place! I must see more of it. Yes, I must!

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: I'm not sure what I was expecting...but now that it's whole, I can't help but feel that it's more of a danger.

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: Yet with the undersea portal destroyed, there's no way to return it whence it came. Whatever should we do now...?

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: Hm? What's this I see?

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: Oh, it's voidsent. There's a few of them in that direction. More of my brethren made it over, it seems. Curious, though─this is much farther than I can usually perceive...

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: I can only assume my vision has improved. Could this be the accumulative effect of our experiences here...?

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: What? It can sense its kind from a vast distance?

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: Amazing! Such an ability would make the task of tracking down invading voidsent a breeze!

dialogue.name: SCOUT04660
dialogue.text: If the creature would agree to assist us in this manner, I'm confident that I can convince my superiors to forge a pact with it!

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: Oho! If it means I can remain in this world, then I'd gladly agree to that arrangement!

dialogue.name: HECTEYES
dialogue.text: I can't say how much I'm indebted to you, mortal. Working with this fellow here, I'll find a way to communicate with your kind and make myself useful. Thank you for everything!

obj.n: Somewhere in the World (Ambitions Writhe) Orchestrion Roll
